Sentencas: An anode-supported micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) is analyzed by a two-dimensional axisymmetric numerical model, which is validated with the experimental I-V data.
Titulo: Thermal stress modeling of anode supported micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The temperature distribution generated by the thermo-electrochemical model is used to calculate the thermal stress field in the tubular SOFC.
Titulo: Thermal stress modeling of anode supported micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The results indicate that the current transport in the anode is the same at every investigated position.
Titulo: Thermal stress modeling of anode supported micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The stress of the micro-tubular cell occurs mainly because of the residual stress due to the mismatch between the coefficients of thermal expansion of the materials of the membrane electrode assembly.
Titulo: Thermal stress modeling of anode supported micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The micro-tubular cell can operate safely, but if there is an interfacial defect or a high enough tensile stress applied at the electrolyte, a failure can arise.
Titulo: Thermal stress modeling of anode supported micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell
